parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of propulsion power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning message "Propulsion Power Reduced" or "Loss of Propulsion" appears on the display
sudden loss of acceleration
inability to shift gears
jolting or stalling of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down or lose critical functions, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
failure of the instrument cluster
navigation system
or backup camera
inability to charge the vehicle
warning lights or messages on the display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause the vehicle to malfunction or lose critical functions, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning messages or lights on the display
failure of the airbag system
seat belt pretensioner
or other safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging system can cause the vehicle to not charge properly, increasing the risk of running out of power or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Inability to charge the vehicle
warning messages or lights on the display
overheating of the charging station.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Passenger Presence Sensor (PPS) can cause the suppression of the passenger frontal and knee airbags in the event of a crash, posing a risk of serious injury to passengers.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning message appears on the dashboard
the passenger airbag is not deploying correctly
the airbag system is malfunctioning
the PPS sensor mat is bunching or folding
causing an increased resistance in the sensor mat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or come to a complete stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or comes to a complete stop without warning
often accompanied by a "Propulsion System Failure" message on the display screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to experience limited acceleration, making it difficult to merge onto highways or climb hills, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences limited acceleration
taking an abnormally long time to reach normal speeds
often accompanied by a slow display of speed on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause the loss of critical vehicle functions, including charging control, voice command, stereo, climate control, and reverse camera, which can increase the risk of accidents and reduce vehicle safety.
symptoms: The center console is blank
and the computer controlling the screen fails to boot
resulting in the loss of various vehicle functions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even fires, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
and the coolant level is low or empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The error in gear selection can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The vehicle's gear selector overshoots into neutral
causing the vehicle to lose power or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or mushy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle does not stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake shoes can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or mushy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle does not stop or slows down unexpectedly
the brake shoes separate into two pieces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or mushy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal does not respond to pressure
the vehicle does not stop or slows down unexpectedly.
